# Software Requirements Specification (SRS)

## Project Overview

The goal of this project is to provide a demo e-commerce web application (saucedemo.com) that allows users to log in, browse products, manage a shopping cart, and complete purchases.

---

## Functional Requirements

### FR-001: User Login

- The system must allow users to log in with a valid username and password.
- The system must display an error message for invalid credentials.
- The system must log out users and end the session securely.

### FR-002: Product Catalog

- Users must be able to view a list of available products after logging in.
- Each product must display a name, image, price, and description.
- Users must be able to sort products by name or price.

### FR-003: Shopping Cart

- Users must be able to add products to the shopping cart from the product list.
- Users must be able to view the cart with all selected items, quantities, and prices.
- Users must be able to remove items from the cart.

### FR-004: Checkout Process

- Users must be able to proceed to checkout from the cart.
- The system must collect user information (first name, last name, postal code) during checkout.
- The system must display an order summary before finalizing the purchase.
- The system must confirm the order and display a success message after checkout.

### FR-005: Logout

- Users must be able to log out from any page.
- The system must redirect users to the login page after logout.

---

## Non-Functional Requirements

- The application must be responsive and work on desktop and mobile browsers.
- The system must provide clear error messages for invalid actions.
- The application must load product and cart data within 2 seconds.

---

## Business Rules

- Only logged-in users can add products to the cart or proceed to checkout.
- Users cannot proceed to checkout with an empty cart.
- All required user information must be provided to complete checkout.

---

## Acceptance Criteria

- Users can log in with valid credentials and are redirected to the products page.
- Invalid login attempts display an appropriate error message.
- Products are displayed with correct details and sorting options.
- Cart operations (add, remove, view) work as expected.
- Checkout flow completes only with all required information.
- Successful checkout displays a confirmation message.
- Users can log out and are redirected to the login page.
